&quot;Late in 1814, the first road into the Hartley Valley, at that time unnamed, was built by William Cox. His primitive highway crossed the Blue Mountains and descended Mount York b y a steep and rugged pass. Once in the valley the road went northerly for a shirt distance, then south-westerly, running about midway between the river and the foot of the Blue Mountains.&quot;

Source: &quot;Hartley and its Historic Court-House&quot; 

